Sentencas: Electrode materials which exhibit high conductivities in both oxidising and reducing atmospheres are in high demand for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) and solid oxide electrolytic cells (SOECs).
Titulo: A perovskite oxide with high conductivities in both air and reducing atmosphere for use as electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this paper, we investigated Cu-doped SrFe0.9Nb0.1O3-delta finding that the primitive perovskite oxide SrFe0.8Cu0.1Nb0.1O3-delta (SFCN) exhibits a conductivity of 63 Scm(-1)and 60 Scm(-1) at 415 degrees C in air and 5% H-2/Ar respectively.
Titulo: A perovskite oxide with high conductivities in both air and reducing atmosphere for use as electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is believed that the high conductivity in 5% H-2/Ar is related to the exsolved Fe (or FeCu alloy) on exposure to a reducing atmosphere.
Titulo: A perovskite oxide with high conductivities in both air and reducing atmosphere for use as electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To the best of our knowledge, the conductivity of SrFe0.8Cu0.1Nb0.1O3-delta in a reducing atmosphere is the highest of all reported oxides which also exhibit a high conductivity in air.
Titulo: A perovskite oxide with high conductivities in both air and reducing atmosphere for use as electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Fuel cell performance using SrFe0.8Cu0.1Nb0.1O3-delta as the anode, (Y2O3)(0.08)(ZrO2)(0.92) as the electrolyte and La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-delta as the cathode achieved a power density of 423 mWcm(-2)
Titulo: A perovskite oxide with high conductivities in both air and reducing atmosphere for use as electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: at 700 degrees C indicating that SFCN is a promising anode for SOFCs.
Titulo: A perovskite oxide with high conductivities in both air and reducing atmosphere for use as electrode for solid oxide fuel cells
